[src:stochastic-calculus/girsanov-theorem] The measure *Q* constructed above is not equivalent to *P* on ${\mathcal {F}}_{\infty }$ as this would only be the case if the Radon–Nikodym derivative were a uniformly integrable martingale, which the exponential martingale described above is not.
[src:stochastic-calculus/girsanov-theorem] On the other hand, as long as Novikov's condition is satisfied the measures are equivalent on ${\mathcal {F}}_{T}$ .
